title: Namias of Arizona Recalls Chicken Products Due To Misbranding and Undeclared Allergens
summary: WASHINGTON, March 3, 2016 Namias of Arizona, Inc., a Tucson, Ariz. establishment, is recalling approximately 19,200 pounds of chicken products due to misbranding and an undeclared allergen, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
